    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-31T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/67<hi rend="superscript">9/24</hi>:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-31T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 31, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>89. From the Under Secretary. After careful consideration of your suggestions the
                    Department has decided, in view of immigration and other regulations of the
                    intermediate countries en route to Chile and the desirability of protection of
                    their persons and effects from unnecessary inquisitiveness or embarrassing
                    formalities on their travels subsequent to leaving Chile, that the two officers
                    concerned should travel on special passports stating merely that they are
                    proceeding abroad on official business for their respective departments. They
                    have however been specifically enjoined not to use their credentials as
                    diplomatic couriers except in case of absolute necessity. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
